Played a lot in my youth but I lost interest in the abstract strategy genre after I discovered games rooted in history. A game’s theme, or story, has become a deciding factor in my enjoyment.

Reasons to love chess:
• a centuries long tradition and tournament history;
• cross-cultural and international appeal;
• nostalgia (many happy childhood memories associated with this game);
• appeals to a certain ultra competitive cerebral personality type;
• a solid abstract design for puzzle aficionados;
• simple rules;
• low cost of entry;
• the physical components are pleasant to handle, and can be made into art in and of themselves.
